ives for criticism and philosophy. Representation and Its Discontents identifies the legacy of this formative moment in modern criticism and suggests its relevance to contemporary discussions of post-structuralism, orientalism, theories of textuality, and the nature of philosophical discourse.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCriticismzGermanyxHistory. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismy18th century. 0aGerman literaturexHistory and criticismy19th century. 0aGerman literaturey18th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGerman literaturey19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aRomanticismzGermany. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh  a18th century german literature.  a18th century german philosophy.  aaesthetics.  acontemporary philosophy.  acritical intervention.  acritical theory.  acultural interpretation.  acultural studies.  afriedrich schlegel.  agerman idealism.  agerman romanticism.  ahermeneutics.  aliterary tales.  aliterary theory.  aludwig achim von arnim.  anature of knowledge.  anovalis.  aorientalism.  aphilosophical discourse.  aphilosophical revolution.  apost structuralism.  arepresentation.  asystematicity.  atemporality.  atheory of textuality.  atranscendental philosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052007676140uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520912083?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520912083423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520912083/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY